      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests on canonical rotating-machinery benchmarks confirm solver implementation is free of coding errors at required gradation.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to rotating-frame Navier-Stokes equations yields observed order 1.97 (expected 2.0); discrepancy within accepted tolerance. Code verification is complete at gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI on three systematically refined meshes yields discretization uncertainty below 5% of hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "Three meshes (4.2M, 11.8M, 31.4M cells) produce GCI of 3.1% on normalized hemolysis index at the design point. Achieved level 4 satisfies MRL 5 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature) are documented with measurement uncertainty and match simulation inputs within 2%.",
      "rationale": "In vitro test conditions are logged with calibrated instrumentation (±0.8% flow, ±0.2% speed). Simulation boundary conditions are set to measured means; deviations are within tolerance. Test condition gradation 3 is achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric (E_rms normalized by experimental uncertainty) is below 1.0 across all 5 operating points for the hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "E_rms/U_exp = 0.71 across the five VAD operating points, indicating model predictions fall within experimental uncertainty bands. Achieved level 4 meets the MRL 5 requirement for output comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI used in validation (normalized hemolysis index, NIH) directly maps to the clinical decision threshold without surrogate substitution.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the regulatory-accepted hemolysis metric and is computed directly from CFD stress history via the Giersiepen power-law model. No surrogate QoI is introduced. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments are conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under VAD-representative flow-speed combinations; fluid properties match clinical blood analog within specified tolerances.",
      "rationale": "All five validation operating points are drawn from the VAD clinical envelope. The FDA generic pump geometry is the same geometry used in the COU prediction. Porcine blood analog (hematocrit 33±2%) matches clinical range. Achieved level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence is demonstrated by residual reduction of at least 5 orders of magnitude and stabilization of QoI monitor to within 0.1% over final 500 iterations.",
      "rationale": "All five operating-point simulations achieve mass residual below 1e-6 and hemolysis index monitor variation below 0.05% over the final 500 iterations. Solver error gradation 3 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of simulation setup, boundary condition application, and post-processing scripts is documented and all identified errors are resolved.",
      "rationale": "Two independent engineers reviewed the simulation setup checklist and post-processing pipeline. Three minor errors in boundary condition labeling were identified and corrected prior to final runs. Use error gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection is justified by comparison of at least two model forms against benchmark flow-field data; selected model is documented with supporting evidence.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega and realizable k-epsilon turbulence models were compared against FDA pump PIV data. SST k-omega produced lower velocity RMSE (4.2% vs. 7.8%) and was selected. Model form justification is documented. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters are characterized with probability distributions; a comprehensive Monte Carlo propagation across all uncertain inputs is performed and the resulting output uncertainty is reported.",
      "rationale": "Twelve model input parameters (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, blood viscosity, hematocrit, power-law coefficients alpha and beta, wall roughness, and five geometric tolerances) are assigned probability distributions derived from measurement data and literature. A 10,000-sample Latin hypercube Monte Carlo propagation is executed; the 95th-percentile hemolysis index prediction interval is reported as ±18% of the mean prediction. Comprehensive UQ coverage across all inputs is confirmed. Achieved level 4 meets the MRL 5 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least three independently fabricated pump samples are tested; sample-to-sample variability is quantified and reported.",
      "rationale": "Four independently machined FDA pump specimens were tested. Coefficient of variation in hemolysis index across specimens is 4.3%, indicating acceptable manufacturing consistency. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters used in validation activities are demonstrably equivalent to those used in the COU prediction, with any differences quantified and shown to have negligible impact.",
      "rationale": "Validation and COU simulations share identical mesh topology, solver settings, and boundary condition protocols. The only difference is fluid temperature (22°C validation vs. 37°C COU); viscosity correction is applied and sensitivity of hemolysis index to this difference is quantified as less than 1.2%. Equivalency gradation 3 is satisfied."
    }
  ],
